à²¡à²¾. à²Žà²‚. à²¬à²¿. à²ªà²¾à²Ÿà³€à²², à²œà²²à²¸à²‚à²ªà²¨à³à²®à³‚à²² à²¹à²¾à²—à³‚ à²µà²¿à²œà²¯à²ªà³à²° à²œà²¿à²²à³à²²à²¾ à²‰à²¸à³à²¤à³à²µà²¾à²°à²¿ à²¸à²šà²¿à²µà²°à³  Tank filling projects have been a major boon for rain-fed and drought-prone areas. Besides providing drinking water to the people and livestock and improving  groundwater tables in these regions, tanks also attract animals, birds and other fauna. Watching animals and birds drinking water from the once parched lakes of Vijayapura is indeed a beautiful sight.  The tank filling projects are being carried out in Koppal, Bagalkot, Mysuru, Yadgir, Belgaum, Vijayapura, Chikballapura, Mandva, Raichur, Uttara Kannada, Udupi, Mangaluru, Chitradurga and Tumkurur districts among others. While some of the projects have been completed, other projects are in various stages of completion.  - Dr. M. B. Patil, Water Resources & Vijayapura District In-charge Minister
